<font color=#00FF00>Season 05 Episode 02</font>
Title: <font color=#FFFF00>" Big House Part-2"</font>

01:36.852 --> 01:40.403
♪♪

01:40.641 --> 01:44.128
♪♪

01:44.185 --> 01:47.685
♪♪

01:54.623 --> 01:56.988
A 300 call number in
the fine arts section?

01:57.085 --> 01:58.523
What is this, Beirut?

01:58.596 --> 02:00.907
You know,
you don't work here.

02:01.028 --> 02:02.740
You don't have
to reshelve the books.

02:02.798 --> 02:04.768
Well, someone has to.

02:04.843 --> 02:06.980
I'm so sorry. I'm just
really stressed out.

02:07.039 --> 02:09.675
You're a great librarian, and
I'm sure you're not the one

02:09.741 --> 02:11.392
- who shelved this section.
- I am.

02:11.450 --> 02:14.363
God, Debbie, what is going on with you?

02:21.154 --> 02:23.426
Debbie? Is that you?

02:24.276 --> 02:26.398
Are you mad? Because I think

02:26.456 --> 02:27.590
I've been more than fair.

02:27.648 --> 02:29.044
Hello, Detective Santiago.

02:29.109 --> 02:31.506
- Ah, no need for the gun.
- I'm not here to hurt you.

02:31.655 --> 02:33.047
My name is Seamus Murphy.

02:33.105 --> 02:35.971
Yeah, I know who you are.
Every cop in the city does.

02:36.337 --> 02:37.869
- What do you want, Seamus?
- To help.

02:38.010 --> 02:39.569
I know your boyfriend got framed.

02:39.869 --> 02:41.439
Maybe I could give you
the proof you need

02:41.496 --> 02:43.067
to take down the cop
that set him up.

02:43.130 --> 02:44.393
You have something on Hawkins?

02:44.451 --> 02:46.122
She's about to move
5-million dollars' worth

02:46.179 --> 02:48.301
of stolen diamonds...
stones that tie her

02:48.376 --> 02:50.511
to the robberies.
I could tell you

02:50.650 --> 02:52.703
- how to find them.
- Why would you do that?

02:52.882 --> 02:55.389
'Cause I wanna be friends.
I do you a favor,

02:55.630 --> 02:58.225
and one day, you do me a favor.

02:58.894 --> 03:00.705
I don't know. Think about it.

03:01.905 --> 03:03.595
But don't think too hard, huh?

03:04.216 --> 03:06.066
You only got three days.

03:10.085 --> 03:11.676
Forgive me, books.

03:12.906 --> 03:13.997
Oh, God.

03:14.367 --> 03:16.100
So, how was your first
stint in solitary?

03:16.515 --> 03:18.088
It was nothing.
I held it together.

03:18.255 --> 03:20.718
Oh... Amy.

03:20.776 --> 03:22.178
When'd you get here?

03:22.271 --> 03:26.231
You've come for my
conjugal capabilities.

03:26.289 --> 03:28.782
You're looking real good, girl.

03:28.992 --> 03:30.824
Whoa, lost a booby.

03:30.882 --> 03:33.933
No matter.
I'll just build another one.

03:34.076 --> 03:37.348
More mashed potatoes!

03:37.432 --> 03:40.069
So, what happened with that
sweet intel I gave you?

03:40.136 --> 03:43.242
Your tip was garbage. We
busted Romero's delivery.

03:43.404 --> 03:45.879
Get this...
nothing but toothbrushes,

03:45.937 --> 03:49.595
- shampoo, and soap.
- Ooh, lemon verbena.

03:49.653 --> 03:51.395
- Can I keep this?
- Yes, you should... you reek.

03:51.452 --> 03:52.521
'Cause you put me in the hole.

03:52.578 --> 03:54.214
- Have you ever heard of Blizz?
- Yeah, the drug, right?

03:54.271 --> 03:55.936
Uh-huh.
And thanks to your pal Romero,

03:55.994 --> 03:58.582
it's taking over the prison.
I need you to find out

03:58.697 --> 04:00.624
- where he keeps his stash.
- Well,

04:00.701 --> 04:02.943
I doubt he would tell me that.
I'm not exactly

04:03.001 --> 04:04.511
- in the inner circle.
- Maybe you just need

04:04.568 --> 04:07.240
some extra incentive.
Find the stash,

04:07.298 --> 04:09.053
or I'll tell everybody
you're a snitch.

04:09.111 --> 04:11.326
What? No.
They'll kill me.

04:11.413 --> 04:13.273
You don't want that, right?
It'd probably be a lot of

04:13.330 --> 04:14.830
- paperwork for you.
- Oh, it's not.

04:14.888 --> 04:17.791
It's just one form, and
it's already filled out.

04:17.922 --> 04:20.892
We just have to staple a
picture of your corpse to it.

04:21.767 --> 04:24.679
Great.
Prison... is great.

04:26.393 --> 04:28.197
He said I have three days to decide.

04:28.391 --> 04:30.392
We should tread lightly.
Seamus Murphy is the head

04:30.478 --> 04:32.124
of the most brutal crime
family in New York.

04:32.181 --> 04:34.197
This is bad.
This is really, really bad.

04:34.316 --> 04:35.517
Are you concerned about
Seamus Murphy,

04:35.574 --> 04:36.978
Detective Scully, or
were you having trouble

04:37.035 --> 04:39.400
- with the jumble?
- Oh... the first one.

04:39.510 --> 04:41.281
Murphy didn't ask me to
do anything illegal.

04:41.339 --> 04:42.951
He just wants me
to owe him a favor.

04:43.009 --> 04:44.209
Right, but we don't want to
be indebted

04:44.266 --> 04:45.820
- to a man like this.
- I understand,

04:45.878 --> 04:47.624
but we've been watching
Hawkins for a month,

04:47.682 --> 04:49.904
and we have nothing to connect
her to the robberies.

04:50.080 --> 04:52.200
Maybe we should
pursue other routes.

04:52.258 --> 04:55.458
Um, some of us are already
pursuing other routes, Amy.

04:55.516 --> 04:58.070
This is Charles Boyle,
and you're listening to

04:58.165 --> 05:01.904
"Detective Peralta: A God in Shackles."

05:02.067 --> 05:05.778
But first: this podcast is
brought to you by Fun Frames...

05:05.847 --> 05:08.043
make your spectacles a spectacle.

05:08.170 --> 05:09.781
And how is your podcast
supposed to

05:09.848 --> 05:10.850
get Jake out of prison?

05:10.917 --> 05:12.052
I lay out the facts,

05:12.119 --> 05:13.413
people see he was framed.

05:13.471 --> 05:16.146
I build an audience. I get
a celebrity listener.

05:16.259 --> 05:18.617
It's Debra Messing.
She tweets a link.

05:18.675 --> 05:20.755
- Now Sean Hayes is involved.
- Boyle, that's enough.

05:20.823 --> 05:22.836
I know dealing with a
criminal is bad news,

05:22.894 --> 05:25.036
but I can't just let
Jake sit in prison.

05:25.094 --> 05:27.162
Okay, maybe we can figure
out what Murphy knows

05:27.220 --> 05:30.174
without taking his deal.
He says that Hawkins is

05:30.232 --> 05:31.653
moving the diamonds in three days.

05:31.711 --> 05:33.640
That's a new lead.
Let's work it

05:33.698 --> 05:35.293
instead of putting your
career in jeopardy.

05:35.350 --> 05:37.587
- Okay, let's give it a shot.
- Whoo-hoo!

05:37.960 --> 05:40.075
That was also not about the jumble. And

05:40.179 --> 05:41.840
we're all excited about the same thing.

05:41.935 --> 05:43.772
♪♪ <i>Purposeful Tune...</i>

05:43.907 --> 05:45.534
- Did you miss me?
- Oh, my God!

05:45.591 --> 05:46.631
It's Jake! Don't kill me!

05:46.689 --> 05:48.427
- I was just doing Batman!
- What's wrong with you?

05:48.484 --> 05:49.499
Never sneak up on me.

05:49.557 --> 05:50.998
- I was sharpening my shiv.
- Right, I'm sorry.

05:51.055 --> 05:52.123
It's prison. I forgot.

05:52.181 --> 05:53.516
What's up? I'm busy, bitch.

05:53.650 --> 05:57.305
Ah! Well,
all that time in the hole kind of

05:57.363 --> 05:59.955
got me thinking: I'm clearly
gonna be here for a while.

06:00.016 --> 06:02.820
I wanna live my best
prison life, and for me,

06:02.903 --> 06:04.506
that means doing more for the gang.

06:04.564 --> 06:06.223
Now I was thinking,
specifically, I'd be great

06:06.280 --> 06:07.480
in and around the world of drugs,

06:07.537 --> 06:10.331
because, let's be honest:
I'm not great at murder.

06:10.434 --> 06:12.134
- What do you think?
- Nah, that's okay.

06:12.192 --> 06:14.194
- I don't need any help.
- Totally, totally.

06:14.328 --> 06:16.591
You're great at what you do.
You don't need me.

06:16.775 --> 06:19.864
But, maybe... I could learn from you.

06:20.015 --> 06:21.803
You know?
Sort of shadow you for a while

06:21.861 --> 06:22.908
and see
how your operation runs.

06:22.965 --> 06:26.062
Go from... bitch to boss,
as it were.

06:26.149 --> 06:28.019
Jake,
you stop pushing it.

06:28.183 --> 06:30.512
You're gonna make me
think you're a snitch.

06:30.570 --> 06:32.132
And you know
what I do to snitches?

06:32.233 --> 06:33.672
Give them a public dressing down?

06:33.730 --> 06:34.866
Castrate them.

06:34.923 --> 06:36.771
And then I kick 'em to death.

06:37.403 --> 06:42.043
Cool... cool, specific policy.
Love the attitude, love you,

06:42.118 --> 06:43.897
love all of this... okay, see you

06:43.967 --> 06:45.487
in the mess hall, Romero. Bye, Romero.

06:48.546 --> 06:51.307
Hey, I'm in a bind.
I need your help.

06:51.374 --> 06:53.816
- That's what friends are for.
- Well, "friends" might be

06:53.874 --> 06:54.971
a bit of a stretch.
I mean, you're a cannibal

06:55.029 --> 06:56.580
- that ate six people.
- 9 1/2.

06:56.647 --> 06:58.373
Yup, worse. All right,
here are my options:

06:58.432 --> 07:00.596
A, I keep pestering Romero to
tell me where the drugs are,

07:00.653 --> 07:02.454
he realizes I'm a snitch,
then he castrates me

07:02.512 --> 07:04.179
- and kicks me to death.
- That's not great.

07:04.236 --> 07:06.269
- What's option B?
- I back off Romero, never find

07:06.327 --> 07:07.794
out where the drugs are,
the warden tells everyone

07:07.851 --> 07:10.090
I'm a snitch,
and then Romero castrates me

07:10.148 --> 07:12.377
- and kicks me to death.
- Mm, both options sound...

07:12.435 --> 07:14.538
A little castrate-y?
Yeah, that's what I keep

07:14.596 --> 07:16.474
- bumping up against too.
- Well, you know, whenever

07:16.532 --> 07:18.926
I'm backed into a corner,
I just do what I do best:

07:19.085 --> 07:21.300
I drive across country,
forge a new identity,

07:21.358 --> 07:22.954
and then take a job
as a camp counselor.

07:23.011 --> 07:25.303
Oh, my God. Caleb,
you're a genius.

07:25.370 --> 07:27.172
I wouldn't say genius.
That camp ran

07:27.230 --> 07:28.888
a pretty extensive
background check.

07:28.946 --> 07:30.946
No, not that... your past
is a straight-up nightmare,

07:31.003 --> 07:33.045
but... I need to do "what I do best":

07:33.116 --> 07:34.903
be a cop, work the case,

07:34.961 --> 07:36.577
figure out where the
drugs are on my own.

07:36.635 --> 07:38.436
And you tell the warden,
and the warden will

07:38.494 --> 07:39.966
- bust Romero.
- And Romero won't think

07:40.023 --> 07:41.751
I'm a snitch, because he never
told me where they are.

07:41.808 --> 07:42.930
All right,
this is gonna be tough.

07:42.987 --> 07:44.161
I'm really gonna have
to thread the needle.

07:44.218 --> 07:46.126
Ooh! I got really good
at threading needles.

07:46.184 --> 07:47.783
Back when you were making
your skin suit, I know.

07:47.840 --> 07:49.332
Look, I like being friends
with you, but you have to

07:49.389 --> 07:50.716
- stop bringing that up.
- But we're friends?

07:52.396 --> 07:53.897
<i>Moving $5 million in diamonds</i>

07:53.955 --> 07:55.323
is not an everyday activity,

07:55.390 --> 07:57.260
so Hawkins must be
altering her behavior.

07:57.327 --> 07:58.967
She's not. I've been
tailing her for days.

07:59.031 --> 08:00.905
Scully and I went out
to Flaxton Hill Farms

08:00.963 --> 08:02.883
to watch the guy who
testified for Hawkins.

08:02.941 --> 08:04.406
All he does is feed his pigs.

08:04.473 --> 08:06.009
They eat seven or eight meals
a day...

08:06.076 --> 08:08.573
sometimes by force.
They're living the dream.

08:08.631 --> 08:09.876
You know they get slaughtered.

08:09.934 --> 08:11.504
- Worth it.
- Hey, I think

08:11.562 --> 08:13.570
I found something interesting.
I was double-checking

08:13.627 --> 08:15.134
last month's surveillance photos,

08:15.192 --> 08:16.394
and I noticed this.

08:16.577 --> 08:18.275
Hawkins has two different phones:

08:18.338 --> 08:19.807
her normal cell,
and then this one

08:19.865 --> 08:22.469
that only has one app on the
home screen... Snapchat.

08:22.536 --> 08:25.998
Oh, she's up to something.
Snapchat messages disappear.

08:26.093 --> 08:28.371
You can send anything to anybody,

08:28.429 --> 08:30.773
and after they see it,
it's like I never sent it.

08:30.852 --> 08:32.727
Nobody ask Hitchcock
why he knows that.

08:32.823 --> 08:34.703
Could we put a mirroring
app on her phone

08:34.760 --> 08:36.136
so we could
watch everything she does?

08:36.193 --> 08:38.687
Oh, those work great,
but you have to physically

08:38.806 --> 08:39.980
have her phone to install it.

08:40.061 --> 08:42.173
Nobody ask Hitchcock
why he knows that.

08:42.293 --> 08:43.684
I know
how we can get Hawkins' phone.

08:43.741 --> 08:45.033
We get her to visit prison.

08:45.145 --> 08:46.946
They make you leave
your phone in your car.

08:47.004 --> 08:48.604
I wanted to record Jake for the podcast,

08:48.664 --> 08:50.616
but they said I couldn't.
I had to have Terry on

08:50.674 --> 08:52.358
- as a guest.
- I gave up my Saturday

08:52.425 --> 08:53.727
for that. You said I did great.

08:53.794 --> 08:55.106
I'm the host. I have to say that.

08:55.163 --> 08:56.530
So, all we need to do is get

08:56.597 --> 08:58.435
Hawkins to visit someone in
prison.

08:58.502 --> 09:01.088
No, absolutely not.
What would I even say to her?

09:01.146 --> 09:02.517
Well, perhaps you could
ask her to put in

09:02.574 --> 09:03.887
a good word for you with the warden,

09:03.944 --> 09:05.951
- so you can get extra yard time.
- So, you want me to beg

09:06.008 --> 09:08.041
the woman I hate for mercy.
Cool.

09:08.152 --> 09:10.042
Oh, one problem.
How do I stop myself

09:10.100 --> 09:11.671
from smashing through
the glass and squeezing

09:11.728 --> 09:13.493
the life out of her
with my bare hands?

09:13.560 --> 09:15.809
Maybe you could just imagine
doing that.

09:15.867 --> 09:18.020
It'd be probably just as fun
as actually doing it, right?

09:18.077 --> 09:19.268
- No.
- I'm with Diaz.

09:19.326 --> 09:20.995
Imagination is never the solution.

09:21.152 --> 09:23.741
We just need three minutes
to get inside her car

09:23.899 --> 09:25.648
and install the app.

09:25.965 --> 09:28.285
Okay. I can grovel for three minutes.

09:28.356 --> 09:30.183
- But one second more...
- Yes, yes, we know.

09:30.247 --> 09:32.171
You burst through the glass and
squeeze the life out of her

09:32.228 --> 09:35.467
with your bare hands. Well...
I think we have a plan.

09:38.839 --> 09:40.978
Don't let them see us. Blend in.

09:41.036 --> 09:43.770
I gotta tell you, cop work
is a lot like cannibal work.

09:43.881 --> 09:45.249
- Really?
- Oh, yeah.

09:45.316 --> 09:46.944
The watching...

09:47.359 --> 09:49.174
the following...

09:50.686 --> 09:52.951
The waiting for soccer practice
to end.

09:53.009 --> 09:54.571
Come on, man.

09:56.868 --> 09:58.622
Did you see that? Romero just went

09:58.701 --> 10:00.090
into the showers for
the second time today.

10:00.147 --> 10:01.649
Well, maybe he just likes to relax.

10:01.753 --> 10:03.326
No one is relaxed in a prison shower.

10:03.406 --> 10:04.694
It's literally the most tense situation

10:04.751 --> 10:05.779
I've ever been in.

10:05.844 --> 10:07.563
What's he doing in there?

10:07.623 --> 10:09.326
That must be where he stashes the Blizz.

10:09.393 --> 10:11.819
Unless he's just having sex...
no, but he's a huge homophobe.

10:11.907 --> 10:13.018
It's where he stashes the Blizz.

10:13.075 --> 10:14.873
But... all homophobes are secretly gay.

10:14.931 --> 10:15.886
You know what?
It doesn't matter.

10:15.944 --> 10:17.440
We'll check it out later,
when he's done.

10:17.497 --> 10:19.272
Hawkins must be through
security by now.

10:19.330 --> 10:21.170
Rosa promised us three minutes, tops.

10:21.315 --> 10:23.004
We'll get the phone. Captain Holt,

10:23.062 --> 10:24.077
can you distract the lot attendant?

10:24.134 --> 10:25.390
I'm not Captain Holt.

10:25.453 --> 10:26.724
I'm Joe Wozniak,

10:26.791 --> 10:28.260
here to see my girl in prison.

10:28.327 --> 10:31.135
And, to help me pass as a straight...

10:32.734 --> 10:34.971
Kevin's rose-shearing hat.

10:35.561 --> 10:37.765
♪♪ <i>Tense Music...</i>

10:38.010 --> 10:40.248
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:40.367 --> 10:41.950
Little Rosa Diaz.

10:42.225 --> 10:44.948
So, I hear you want me to
put in a good word for you

10:45.006 --> 10:46.364
with the warden?

10:46.692 --> 10:48.111
Yes.

10:48.597 --> 10:49.931
"Yes," what?

10:51.329 --> 10:54.200
Yes... please.

10:54.339 --> 10:56.576
I love this.
This is so much fun for me.

10:56.643 --> 10:58.413
- Can I help you?
- I'm just trying

10:58.480 --> 11:00.093
to work up the nerve to see her.

11:00.188 --> 11:02.820
- See who?
- My female wife, Crystal.

11:03.016 --> 11:05.408
I was cheating on her with
a waitress from Wing Sluts

